      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even minimal alcohol consumption in conjunction with your prescribed medication can significantly affect your body's response. Diazepam is metabolized by the liver, and alcohol can impair this process, leading to increased levels of the drug in your bloodstream. This heightened level could go beyond a 'tiny amount' and lead to serious side effects or overdose. The body's reaction varies among individuals, but it is always safer to avoid alcohol when prescribed diazepam. Consider your doctor's advice on sleep aids and non-pharmaceutical options for better rest.",
